(
<bibRefCitation id="362B4B29C965584AFC39F4089396F41C" author="Flores, D. A. &amp; M. M. Diaz &amp; R. M. Barquez" box="[933,1182,1554,1576]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" pagination="579 - 669" refId="ref85635" refString="Flores, D. A., M. M. Diaz, and R. M. Barquez. 2007. Systematics and distribution of marsupials in Argentina: a review. University of California Publications in Zoology 134: 579 - 669." type="journal article" year="2007">Flores et al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Published distribution maps (e.g., Reid,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="520536D8C965584AFD2CF47D9326F4EA" blockId="111.[667,1194,1639,1758]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
28 Because this character is normally quite constant within species, it is noteworthy that 
<specimenCount id="44BCFD51C965584AFC37F49E9329F4A2" box="[939,1057,1667,1687]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
from Paracou, 
<collectingCountry id="2AAD7648C965584AFD07F4819415F49A" box="[667,797,1691,1710]" name="French Guiana" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(AMNH 266451), has a complete anterior cingulum whereas others from the same locality (e.g., AMNH 267362) have an incomplete anterior cingulum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="520536D8C97A5855FF1CF2CF96B9F376" blockId="112.[128,654,213,645]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
1997; 
<bibRefCitation id="362B4B29C97A5855FF55F2CF9517F2DF" author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; M. Dagosto" box="[201,543,213,235]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" pagination="35 - 39" refId="ref86283" refString="Gardner, A. L., and M. Dagosto. 2008 ('' 2007 ''). Tribe Metachirini Reig, Kirsch, and Marshall, 1985. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America. Vol. 1. Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats, 35 - 39. Chicago: Chicago University Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gardner and Dagosto, 2008</bibRefCitation>
) indicate several range disjunctions, but some of these may be artifacts of inadequate collecting effort in suitable habitats.
</paragraph>
